HEADWORD: Contendent
<hw>Con*tend"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>contendens</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <def>An antagonist; a
contestant.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In all notable changes and revolutions the <qex>contendents</qex>
have been still made a prey to the third party.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contender</ent>⟦br⟧
